tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows significantly elevated creatinine, proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, and low urine specific gravity, suggesting impaired renal function with possible nephrotic-range proteinuria and glycosuria not explained by blood glucose or HbA1c. Urine is cloudy and brown with ammoniacal odor, but no evidence of infection. Findings are consistent with advanced renal dysfunction; further nephrological evaluation is recommended.
